text.tspan: Prevalence of developmental intellectual disability in males vs. females,
Share of males versus females with 'idiopathic developmental intellectual disability', which is a category of disorders defined by
delayed or impaired speech, language, motor condition, and visuo-spatial skills. Prevalence has been age-standardized to
compare between countries and with time.
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease
